==English==

===Etymology===
Named after a legendary magical stone in [[w:en:Blarney Castle|Blarney Castle]], Ireland that gives the gift of eloquence. See also [[w:en:Blarney Stone|Blarney Stone]].

{{wikipedia|Blarney}}

===Pronunciation===
*Rhymes: [[Rhymes:English:-ɑː(r)ni|-ɑː(r)ni]]

===Noun===
'''blarney'''

# Ability to [[talk]] [[constantly]].
# Mindless [[chatter]].
#: ''He is full of '''blarney'''.''
# Persuasive [[flattery]] or kind speech. The ability to tell a man to go to hell , in such a way as he will look forward to the trip.

===Verb===
'''blarney'''

#to use blarney

